modules.name: AWS.CloudDirectory
modules.comments:
Amazon Cloud Directory

Amazon Cloud Directory is a component of the AWS Directory Service that simplifies the development and management of cloud-scale web, mobile, and IoT applications. This guide describes the Cloud Directory operations that you can call programmatically and includes detailed information on data types and errors. For information about AWS Directory Services features, see AWS Directory Service and the AWS Directory Service Administration Guide.

declarations.comments: Adds a new Facet to an object.
declarations.title: addFacetToObject

declarations.comments: Copies the input published schema, at the specified version, into the Directory with the same name and version as that of the published schema.
declarations.title: applySchema

declarations.comments:
Attaches an existing object to another object. An object can be accessed in two ways:

  1. Using the path

  2. Using ObjectIdentifier
declarations.title: attachObject

declarations.comments: Attaches a policy object to a regular object. An object can have a limited number of attached policies.
declarations.title: attachPolicy

declarations.comments: Attaches the specified object to the specified index.
declarations.title: attachToIndex

declarations.comments: Attaches a typed link to a specified source and target object. For more information, see Typed link.
declarations.title: attachTypedLink

declarations.comments: Performs all the read operations in a batch.
declarations.title: batchRead

declarations.comments: Performs all the write operations in a batch. Either all the operations succeed or none.
declarations.title: batchWrite

declarations.comments: Creates a Directory by copying the published schema into the directory. A directory cannot be created without a schema.
declarations.title: createDirectory

declarations.comments: Creates a new Facet in a schema. Facet creation is allowed only in development or applied schemas.
declarations.title: createFacet

declarations.comments: Creates an index object. See Indexing for more information.
declarations.title: createIndex

declarations.comments: Creates an object in a Directory. Additionally attaches the object to a parent, if a parent reference and LinkName is specified. An object is simply a collection of Facet attributes. You can also use this API call to create a policy object, if the facet from which you create the object is a policy facet.
declarations.title: createObject

declarations.comments:
Creates a new schema in a development state. A schema can exist in three phases:

  • Development: This is a mutable phase of the schema. All new schemas are in the development phase. Once the schema is finalized, it can be published.

  • Published: Published schemas are immutable and have a version associated with them.

  • Applied: Applied schemas are mutable in a way that allows you to add new schema facets. You can also add new, nonrequired attributes to existing schema facets. You can apply only published schemas to directories.
declarations.title: createSchema

declarations.comments: Creates a TypedLinkFacet. For more information, see Typed link.
declarations.title: createTypedLinkFacet

declarations.comments: Deletes a directory. Only disabled directories can be deleted. A deleted directory cannot be undone. Exercise extreme caution when deleting directories.
declarations.title: deleteDirectory

declarations.comments: Deletes a given Facet. All attributes and Rules that are associated with the facet will be deleted. Only development schema facets are allowed deletion.
declarations.title: deleteFacet

declarations.comments: Deletes an object and its associated attributes. Only objects with no children and no parents can be deleted.
declarations.title: deleteObject

declarations.comments: Deletes a given schema. Schemas in a development and published state can only be deleted.
declarations.title: deleteSchema

declarations.comments: Deletes a TypedLinkFacet. For more information, see Typed link.
declarations.title: deleteTypedLinkFacet

declarations.comments: Detaches the specified object from the specified index.
declarations.title: detachFromIndex

declarations.comments: Detaches a given object from the parent object. The object that is to be detached from the parent is specified by the link name.
declarations.title: detachObject

declarations.comments: Detaches a policy from an object.
declarations.title: detachPolicy

declarations.comments: Detaches a typed link from a specified source and target object. For more information, see Typed link.
declarations.title: detachTypedLink

declarations.comments: Disables the specified directory. Disabled directories cannot be read or written to. Only enabled directories can be disabled. Disabled directories may be reenabled.
declarations.title: disableDirectory

declarations.comments: Enables the specified directory. Only disabled directories can be enabled. Once enabled, the directory can then be read and written to.
declarations.title: enableDirectory

declarations.comments: Returns current applied schema version ARN, including the minor version in use.
declarations.title: getAppliedSchemaVersion

declarations.comments: Retrieves metadata about a directory.
declarations.title: getDirectory

declarations.comments: Gets details of the Facet, such as facet name, attributes, Rules, or ObjectType. You can call this on all kinds of schema facets -- published, development, or applied.
declarations.title: getFacet

declarations.comments: Retrieves metadata about an object.
declarations.title: getObjectInformation

declarations.comments: Retrieves a JSON representation of the schema. See JSON Schema Format for more information.
declarations.title: getSchemaAsJson

declarations.comments: Returns the identity attribute order for a specific TypedLinkFacet. For more information, see Typed link.
declarations.title: getTypedLinkFacetInformation

declarations.comments: Lists schema major versions applied to a directory. If SchemaArn is provided, lists the minor version.
declarations.title: listAppliedSchemaArns

declarations.comments: Lists indices attached to the specified object.
declarations.title: listAttachedIndices

declarations.comments: Retrieves each Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of schemas in the development state.
declarations.title: listDevelopmentSchemaArns

declarations.comments: Lists directories created within an account.
declarations.title: listDirectories

declarations.comments: Retrieves attributes attached to the facet.
declarations.title: listFacetAttributes

declarations.comments: Retrieves the names of facets that exist in a schema.
declarations.title: listFacetNames

declarations.comments: Returns a paginated list of all the incoming TypedLinkSpecifier information for an object. It also supports filtering by typed link facet and identity attributes. For more information, see Typed link.
declarations.title: listIncomingTypedLinks

declarations.comments: Lists objects and indexed values attached to the index.
declarations.title: listIndex

declarations.comments: Lists all attributes that are associated with an object.
declarations.title: listObjectAttributes

declarations.comments: Returns a paginated list of child objects that are associated with a given object.
declarations.title: listObjectChildren

declarations.comments:
Retrieves all available parent paths for any object type such as node, leaf node, policy node, and index node objects. For more information about objects, see Directory Structure.

Use this API to evaluate all parents for an object. The call returns all objects from the root of the directory up to the requested object. The API returns the number of paths based on user-defined MaxResults, in case there are multiple paths to the parent. The order of the paths and nodes returned is consistent among multiple API calls unless the objects are deleted or moved. Paths not leading to the directory root are ignored from the target object.
declarations.title: listObjectParentPaths

declarations.comments: Lists parent objects that are associated with a given object in pagination fashion.
declarations.title: listObjectParents

declarations.comments: Returns policies attached to an object in pagination fashion.
declarations.title: listObjectPolicies

declarations.comments: Returns a paginated list of all the outgoing TypedLinkSpecifier information for an object. It also supports filtering by typed link facet and identity attributes. For more information, see Typed link.
declarations.title: listOutgoingTypedLinks

declarations.comments: Returns all of the ObjectIdentifiers to which a given policy is attached.
declarations.title: listPolicyAttachments

declarations.comments: Lists schema major versions for a published schema. If SchemaArn is provided, lists the minor version.
declarations.title: listPublishedSchemaArns

declarations.comments: Returns tags for a resource. Tagging is currently supported only for directories with a limit of 50 tags per directory. All 50 tags are returned for a given directory with this API call.
declarations.title: listTagsForResource

declarations.comments: Returns a paginated list of all attribute definitions for a particular TypedLinkFacet. For more information, see Typed link.
declarations.title: listTypedLinkFacetAttributes

declarations.comments: Returns a paginated list of TypedLink facet names for a particular schema. For more information, see Typed link.
declarations.title: listTypedLinkFacetNames

declarations.comments: Lists all policies from the root of the Directory to the object specified. If there are no policies present, an empty list is returned. If policies are present, and if some objects don't have the policies attached, it returns the ObjectIdentifier for such objects. If policies are present, it returns ObjectIdentifier, policyId, and policyType. Paths that don't lead to the root from the target object are ignored. For more information, see Policies.
declarations.title: lookupPolicy

declarations.comments: Publishes a development schema with a major version and a recommended minor version.
declarations.title: publishSchema

declarations.comments: Allows a schema to be updated using JSON upload. Only available for development schemas. See JSON Schema Format for more information.
declarations.title: putSchemaFromJson

declarations.comments: Removes the specified facet from the specified object.
declarations.title: removeFacetFromObject

declarations.comments: An API operation for adding tags to a resource.
declarations.title: tagResource

declarations.comments: An API operation for removing tags from a resource.
declarations.title: untagResource

declarations.comments:
Does the following:

  1. Adds new Attributes, Rules, or ObjectTypes.

  2. Updates existing Attributes, Rules, or ObjectTypes.

  3. Deletes existing Attributes, Rules, or ObjectTypes.
declarations.title: updateFacet

declarations.comments: Updates a given object's attributes.
declarations.title: updateObjectAttributes

declarations.comments: Updates the schema name with a new name. Only development schema names can be updated.
declarations.title: updateSchema

declarations.comments: Updates a TypedLinkFacet. For more information, see Typed link.
declarations.title: updateTypedLinkFacet

declarations.comments: Upgrades a single directory in-place using the PublishedSchemaArn with schema updates found in MinorVersion. Backwards-compatible minor version upgrades are instantaneously available for readers on all objects in the directory. Note: This is a synchronous API call and upgrades only one schema on a given directory per call. To upgrade multiple directories from one schema, you would need to call this API on each directory.
declarations.title: upgradeAppliedSchema

declarations.comments: Upgrades a published schema under a new minor version revision using the current contents of DevelopmentSchemaArn.
declarations.title: upgradePublishedSchema

declarations.comments: Access denied. Check your permissions.
declarations.title: AccessDeniedException

declarations.comments: A unique identifier for an attribute.
declarations.title: AttributeKey

declarations.comments: The combination of an attribute key and an attribute value.
declarations.title: AttributeKeyAndValue

declarations.comments: Identifies the attribute name and value for a typed link.
declarations.title: AttributeNameAndValue

declarations.title: BatchAddFacetToObject

declarations.comments: The result of a batch add facet to object operation.
declarations.title: BatchAddFacetToObjectResponse

declarations.comments: Represents the output batch AttachObject response operation.
declarations.title: BatchAttachObjectResponse

declarations.comments: Attaches a policy object to a regular object inside a BatchRead operation. For more information, see AttachPolicy and BatchReadRequest$Operations.
declarations.title: BatchAttachPolicy

declarations.comments: Represents the output of an AttachPolicy response operation.
declarations.title: BatchAttachPolicyResponse

declarations.title: BatchDeleteObjectResponse

declarations.comments: Detaches the specified object from the specified index inside a BatchRead operation. For more information, see DetachFromIndex and BatchReadRequest$Operations.
declarations.title: BatchDetachFromIndex

declarations.comments: Represents the output of a DetachFromIndex response operation.

declarations.comments: Represents the output of a DetachObject operation.
declarations.title: BatchDetachObject

declarations.comments: Represents the output of a DetachObject response operation.
declarations.title: BatchDetachObjectResponse

declarations.title: BatchDetachPolicy

declarations.comments: Represents the output of a DetachPolicy response operation.
declarations.title: BatchDetachPolicyResponse

declarations.comments: Detaches a typed link from a specified source and target object inside a BatchRead operation. For more information, see DetachTypedLink and BatchReadRequest$Operations.
declarations.title: BatchDetachTypedLink

declarations.comments: Represents the output of a DetachTypedLink response operation.

declarations.comments: Retrieves metadata about an object inside a BatchRead operation. For more information, see GetObjectInformation and BatchReadRequest$Operations.

declarations.comments: Represents the output of a GetObjectInformation response operation.

declarations.comments: Represents the output of a ListAttachedIndices response operation.
declarations.title: BatchListAttachedIndicesResponse

declarations.title: BatchListIncomingTypedLinks

declarations.comments: Represents the output of a ListIncomingTypedLinks response operation.

declarations.comments: Lists objects attached to the specified index inside a BatchRead operation. For more information, see ListIndex and BatchReadRequest$Operations.

declarations.comments: Represents the output of a ListIndex response operation.
declarations.title: BatchListIndexResponse

declarations.comments: Represents the output of a ListObjectAttributes operation.
declarations.title: BatchListObjectAttributes

declarations.comments: Represents the output of a ListObjectAttributes response operation.
declarations.title: BatchListObjectAttributesResponse

declarations.comments: Represents the output of a ListObjectChildren operation.
declarations.title: BatchListObjectChildren

declarations.comments: Represents the output of a ListObjectChildren response operation.
declarations.title: BatchListObjectChildrenResponse

declarations.comments: Retrieves all available parent paths for any object type such as node, leaf node, policy node, and index node objects inside a BatchRead operation. For more information, see ListObjectParentPaths and BatchReadRequest$Operations.
declarations.title: BatchListObjectParentPaths

declarations.comments: Represents the output of a ListObjectParentPaths response operation.
declarations.title: BatchListObjectParentPathsResponse

declarations.comments: Returns policies attached to an object in pagination fashion inside a BatchRead operation. For more information, see ListObjectPolicies and BatchReadRequest$Operations.
declarations.title: BatchListObjectPolicies

declarations.comments: Represents the output of a ListObjectPolicies response operation.
declarations.title: BatchListObjectPoliciesResponse

declarations.comments: Returns a paginated list of all the outgoing TypedLinkSpecifier information for an object inside a BatchRead operation. For more information, see ListOutgoingTypedLinks and BatchReadRequest$Operations.
declarations.title: BatchListOutgoingTypedLinks

declarations.comments: Represents the output of a ListOutgoingTypedLinks response operation.

declarations.comments: Returns all of the ObjectIdentifiers to which a given policy is attached inside a BatchRead operation. For more information, see ListPolicyAttachments and BatchReadRequest$Operations.
declarations.title: BatchListPolicyAttachments

declarations.comments: Represents the output of a ListPolicyAttachments response operation.

declarations.title: BatchUpdateObjectAttributes

declarations.comments: Represents the output of a BatchUpdate response operation.

declarations.comments: A BatchWrite exception has occurred.
declarations.title: BatchWriteException

declarations.comments: Represents the output of a BatchWrite operation.

declarations.comments: Represents the output of a BatchWrite response operation.
declarations.title: BatchWriteOperationResponse

declarations.comments: Cannot list the parents of a Directory root.
declarations.title: CannotListParentOfRootException

declarations.comments: Directory structure that includes the directory name and directory ARN.
declarations.title: Directory

declarations.comments: Indicates that a Directory could not be created due to a naming conflict. Choose a different name and try again.
declarations.title: DirectoryAlreadyExistsException

declarations.comments: A directory that has been deleted and to which access has been attempted. Note: The requested resource will eventually cease to exist.
declarations.title: DirectoryDeletedException

declarations.comments: An operation can only operate on a disabled directory.
declarations.title: DirectoryNotDisabledException

declarations.comments: An operation can only operate on a directory that is not enabled.
declarations.title: DirectoryNotEnabledException

declarations.comments: A structure that contains Name, ARN, Attributes, Rules, and ObjectTypes.
declarations.title: Facet

declarations.comments: A facet with the same name already exists.
declarations.title: FacetAlreadyExistsException

declarations.comments: An attribute that is associated with the Facet.
declarations.title: FacetAttribute

declarations.comments: A facet attribute definition. See Attribute References for more information.
declarations.title: FacetAttributeDefinition

declarations.comments: The facet attribute reference that specifies the attribute definition that contains the attribute facet name and attribute name.
declarations.title: FacetAttributeReference

declarations.comments: A structure that contains information used to update an attribute.
declarations.title: FacetAttributeUpdate

declarations.comments: Occurs when deleting a facet that contains an attribute that is a target to an attribute reference in a different facet.
declarations.title: FacetInUseException

declarations.comments: The specified Facet could not be found.
declarations.title: FacetNotFoundException

declarations.comments: The Facet that you provided was not well formed or could not be validated with the schema.
declarations.title: FacetValidationException

declarations.comments: Indicates a failure occurred while performing a check for backward compatibility between the specified schema and the schema that is currently applied to the directory.
declarations.title: IncompatibleSchemaException

declarations.comments: Represents an index and an attached object.
declarations.title: IndexAttachment

declarations.comments: An object has been attempted to be attached to an object that does not have the appropriate attribute value.
declarations.title: IndexedAttributeMissingException

declarations.comments: Indicates a problem that must be resolved by Amazon Web Services. This might be a transient error in which case you can retry your request until it succeeds. Otherwise, go to the AWS Service Health Dashboard site to see if there are any operational issues with the service.
declarations.title: InternalServiceException

declarations.comments: Indicates that the provided ARN value is not valid.
declarations.title: InvalidArnException

declarations.comments: Indicates that an attempt to attach an object with the same link name or to apply a schema with the same name has occurred. Rename the link or the schema and then try again.
declarations.title: InvalidAttachmentException

declarations.comments: An attempt to modify a Facet resulted in an invalid schema exception.
declarations.title: InvalidFacetUpdateException

declarations.comments: Indicates that the NextToken value is not valid.
declarations.title: InvalidNextTokenException

declarations.comments: Occurs when any of the rule parameter keys or values are invalid.
declarations.title: InvalidRuleException

declarations.comments: Indicates that the provided SchemaDoc value is not valid.
declarations.title: InvalidSchemaDocException

declarations.comments: Can occur for multiple reasons such as when you tag a resource that doesn’t exist or if you specify a higher number of tags for a resource than the allowed limit. Allowed limit is 50 tags per resource.
declarations.title: InvalidTaggingRequestException

declarations.comments: Indicates that limits are exceeded. See Limits for more information.
declarations.title: LimitExceededException

declarations.comments: Indicates that a link could not be created due to a naming conflict. Choose a different name and then try again.
declarations.title: LinkNameAlreadyInUseException

declarations.comments: Indicates that the requested operation can only operate on index objects.
declarations.title: NotIndexException

declarations.comments: Occurs when any invalid operations are performed on an object that is not a node, such as calling ListObjectChildren for a leaf node object.
declarations.title: NotNodeException

declarations.comments: Indicates that the requested operation can only operate on policy objects.
declarations.title: NotPolicyException

declarations.comments: Indicates that the object is not attached to the index.
declarations.title: ObjectAlreadyDetachedException

declarations.comments: The action to take on the object attribute.
declarations.title: ObjectAttributeAction

declarations.comments: A range of attributes.
declarations.title: ObjectAttributeRange

declarations.comments: Structure that contains attribute update information.
declarations.title: ObjectAttributeUpdate

declarations.comments: Indicates that the requested operation cannot be completed because the object has not been detached from the tree.
declarations.title: ObjectNotDetachedException

declarations.comments: The reference that identifies an object.
declarations.title: ObjectReference

declarations.comments: Returns the path to the ObjectIdentifiers that is associated with the directory.
declarations.title: PathToObjectIdentifiers

declarations.comments: Contains the PolicyType, PolicyId, and the ObjectIdentifier to which it is attached. For more information, see Policies.
declarations.title: PolicyAttachment

declarations.comments: Used when a regular object exists in a Directory and you want to find all of the policies that are associated with that object and the parent to that object.
declarations.title: PolicyToPath

declarations.comments: The specified resource could not be found.
declarations.title: ResourceNotFoundException

declarations.comments: Occurs when a conflict with a previous successful write is detected. For example, if a write operation occurs on an object and then an attempt is made to read the object using “SERIALIZABLE” consistency, this exception may result. This generally occurs when the previous write did not have time to propagate to the host serving the current request. A retry (with appropriate backoff logic) is the recommended response to this exception.
declarations.title: RetryableConflictException

declarations.comments: Contains an Amazon Resource Name (ARN) and parameters that are associated with the rule.
declarations.title: Rule

declarations.comments: Indicates that a schema could not be created due to a naming conflict. Please select a different name and then try again.
declarations.title: SchemaAlreadyExistsException

declarations.comments: Indicates that a schema is already published.
declarations.title: SchemaAlreadyPublishedException

declarations.comments: A facet.
declarations.title: SchemaFacet

declarations.comments: The object could not be deleted because links still exist. Remove the links and then try the operation again.
declarations.title: StillContainsLinksException

declarations.comments: The tag structure that contains a tag key and value.
declarations.title: Tag

declarations.comments: Represents the data for a typed attribute. You can set one, and only one, of the elements. Each attribute in an item is a name-value pair. Attributes have a single value.
declarations.title: TypedAttributeValue

declarations.comments: A range of attribute values.
declarations.title: TypedAttributeValueRange

declarations.comments: A typed link attribute definition.
declarations.title: TypedLinkAttributeDefinition

declarations.comments: Identifies the range of attributes that are used by a specified filter.
declarations.title: TypedLinkAttributeRange

declarations.comments: Defines the typed links structure and its attributes. To create a typed link facet, use the CreateTypedLinkFacet API.
declarations.title: TypedLinkFacet

declarations.comments: A typed link facet attribute update.
declarations.title: TypedLinkFacetAttributeUpdate

declarations.comments: Identifies the schema Amazon Resource Name (ARN) and facet name for the typed link.
declarations.title: TypedLinkSchemaAndFacetName

declarations.comments: Contains all the information that is used to uniquely identify a typed link. The parameters discussed in this topic are used to uniquely specify the typed link being operated on. The AttachTypedLink API returns a typed link specifier while the DetachTypedLink API accepts one as input. Similarly, the ListIncomingTypedLinks and ListOutgoingTypedLinks API operations provide typed link specifiers as output. You can also construct a typed link specifier from scratch.
declarations.title: TypedLinkSpecifier

declarations.comments: Indicates that the requested index type is not supported.
declarations.title: UnsupportedIndexTypeException

declarations.comments: Indicates that your request is malformed in some manner. See the exception message.
declarations.title: ValidationException
